x4freetext: The Decay of the Different Nuclides was
Followed in Most Cases For at Least Six Half Lives.
The Largest Error is Associated with the Calculated
Efficiencies of the Ge(Li) Detector.In Some Cases,
Significant Error Arises from the Uncertainties in the
Branching Intensities and,from the Counting Statistics.
Errors in Estimation of the Areas of the Photopeaks are
Calculated to be Less Than 2% While the Errors in the
Radiochemical Procedures are Even Smaller.The
Compounded Standard Deviation in the Measured Cross
Sections is Estimated to be +-6% Unless Otherwise
Noted.
